# Harbor is PINNED to a tag. The recorded gitlink commit (in the parent repo
# index) is the source of truth — do NOT run `git submodule update --remote`:
# that chases the remote branch and silently drifts the UI lib out from under
# the frontend, which is what broke the app before. To intentionally bump:
#   1) git -C harbor fetch --tags
#   2) git -C harbor checkout <new tag>      (e.g. v0.3.2)
#   3) git add harbor && commit, then update the "Pinned" note below.
# Pinned: v0.3.1
[submodule "harbor"]
	path = harbor
	url = https://github.com/Infinibay/harbor.git
